		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> <date>June 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1862</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Enclosed please<lb/> find &#36;3&#44; which please and place to our<lb/> credit for the Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Samuels Hoffman</persName></p>
				<p>P.S. <persName>Mr T. Haasah</persName> from <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName><lb/> who is a friend of ours&#44; has written So<lb/> as and requested as&#44; So inquire as <placeName>Phi<lb/>ladelphia</placeName>&#44; <sic>wheser</sic> a woman who is about<lb/> 55 <sic>jears</sic> old and who has the best of<lb/> <sic>recomodations</sic>&#44; would be accepted in<lb/> the jewish foster home of your City&#44;<lb/> the woman in reference&#44; is stout and<lb/> hardy&#44; but to religious to agree in<lb/> a private<add>&#63;</add> family of <placeName>Louisville</placeName>.<lb/>  <persName>Mr Haasah</persName> wishes to know under<lb/> what rules and regulations she would<lb/> be accepted&#44; and what kind of work<lb/> she would have to do.  Knowing Sir<lb/> that you and conversant with these<lb/> affairs&#44; we take the liberty to request</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>you&#44; so either answer us the above<lb/> questions or to <persName>Mr Th. Haasah</persName> of<lb/> <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">S. H.</persName></p>
				<p>We omitted to mention&#44; that the<lb/> woman is poor.</p>
		</body>
